---
layout: base.njk
title: Dr. Hadiza Galadima — Biostatistics, Public Health, Pedagogy
description: Dr. Hadiza Galadima — biostatistician at Old Dominion University. Research on statistical methods for public health, teaching of applied biostatistics, and open tools for students.
schemaType: Person
---
<section class="hero">
  <div class="hero-inner">
    <div class="hero-photo-wrap">
      <img src="/assets/photo.svg" alt="Portrait of {{ site.name }}" class="hero-photo" width="180" height="180">
    </div>
    <div class="hero-text">
      <p class="hero-kicker">{{ site.affiliation.department }} · {{ site.affiliation.name }}</p>
      <h1 class="hero-name">{{ site.name }}</h1>
      <p class="hero-role">{{ site.role }}</p>
      <p class="hero-tagline">{{ site.tagline }}</p>
      <p class="hero-actions">
        <a href="/research/" class="button button-primary">Research</a>
        <a href="/teaching/" class="button button-secondary">Teaching</a>
        <a href="/cv/" class="button button-ghost">CV</a>
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="cards">
  <div class="cards-inner">
    <article class="card">
      <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/research/">Research</a></h2>
      <p class="card-description">UPDATE: 1–2 sentence summary of your research focus — e.g., methods for small-sample inference in community-health studies, collaboration with epidemiologists on outcome evaluation.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/teaching/">Teaching</a></h2>
      <p class="card-description">MPHO 605 (Biostatistics) and open-source tools for graduate public-health education. Free calculators at <a href="https://ztchi.hgaladima.com/" rel="noopener">ztchi.hgaladima.com</a>.</p>
    </article>

    <article class="card">
      <h2 class="card-title"><a href="/blog/">Writing</a></h2>
      <p class="card-description">Teaching notes, pedagogy reflections, and research-in-progress essays. Unpolished on purpose — this is where ideas develop.</p>
    </article>
  </div>
</section>

<section class="section-recent">
  <div class="section-inner">
    <h2 class="section-title">Recent posts</h2>
    <ul class="post-list">
      {% for post in collections.posts | reverse | slice(0, 3) %}
        <li class="post-list-item">
          <a href="{{ post.url }}">
            <span class="post-list-date"><time datetime="{{ post.date | isoDate }}">{{ post.date | readableDate }}</time></span>
            <span class="post-list-title">{{ post.data.title }}</span>
          </a>
          {% if post.data.summary %}<p class="post-list-summary">{{ post.data.summary }}</p>{% endif %}
        </li>
      {% endfor %}
    </ul>
    <p><a href="/blog/" class="link-more">All posts &rarr;</a></p>
  </div>
</section>
